shortDescription: A guajillo chili or guajillo chile (chile guajillo in Spanish) is a variety of chile pepper of the species Capsicum annuum which is widely used in the cuisine of Mexico. They are sometimes used to make the salsa for tamales; the dried fruits are seeded, soaked, pulverized to a thin paste, then cooked with salt and several other ingredients to produce a thick, red, flavorful sauce. Guajillo chilies may be used in pastes, butters, or rubs to flavor all kinds of meats, especially chicken. Alternatively, they can be added to salsas to create a sweet side dish with a surprisingly hot finish. In its dried form, chiles can keep for months in a dry, cool place.
longDescription: AUTHENTIC DRIED GUAJILLO CHILES - Guajillo chiles have a sweet, fruity, tangy, smoky flavor profile with notes of berries and tea. The Guajillo Chile is the dried form of Mirasol Chile. ADD MILD HEAT TO YOUR DISHES - Guajillo chiles have a mild heat, registering 2,500 to 5,000 on the Scoville scale. The Guajillo chile is one of the most used chile peppers in Mexican gastronomy to give color and flavor to sauces, moles, marinades, and a lot of other stews. GROWN IN THE FIELDS OF MEXICO - Grown in the beautiful fields of Mexico to ensure freshness and authenticity. Our chiles are sourced from real farmers to bring authentic and fresh chiles to your table. ALL NATURAL, NO CHEMICALS - Our recipe includes NO preservatives, additives, or chemicals to ensure real freshness. Quality is our foremost priority! PACKED WITH CARE - Our Guajillo chilies are hand-selected and hand-packed in our gourmet spice shop. For optimum flavor and freshness, we recommend washing all chiles before being consumed.

name: Dried Chipotle Chile Peppers - Whole - 4 oz Resealable Bag by Ole Rico
shortDescription: Chipotle Chiles are an authentic product sourced from the best spice houses in Mexico. They are dry smoked jalapeño peppers used in many authentic Mexican dishes, as well as an added ingredient to salsas, chili, meats, soups, BBQ, etc. Chipotle Chile Peppers are 2 to 4 inches in length, about 1 inch wide. Because of how Chipotle Chile peppers are processed, they come with a more "fruity" and rich, smokey flavor with a medium hot profile, typically categorized on a 5,000 to 10,000 Scoville Scale. In Latin countries, it's the preferred chile for making dry salsa, or also known as Salsa Seca. Chipotle is often a key ingredient in a recipe that imparts a relatively mild but earthy spiciness to many dishes in Mexican cuisine.
longDescription: AUTHENTIC DRIED MORITA CHILES - The chipotle chile is one of the most popular chilies at a national and international level and without a doubt a condiment that most of the people of Mexico love and know. ADD FLAVOR TO YOUR DISHES - One of the most popular dishes prepared with these chilies is the famous Tinga, a Mexican dish made with shredded chicken in a sauce made from tomatoes, chipotle chilis in adobo, and sliced onions. name: Dried Guajillo Chiles - Whole - 8 oz Resealable Bag by Ole Rico
shortDescription: A guajillo chili or guajillo chile (chile guajillo in Spanish) is a variety of chile pepper of the species Capsicum annuum which is widely used in the cuisine of Mexico. They are sometimes used to make the salsa for tamales; the dried fruits are seeded, soaked, pulverized to a thin paste, then cooked with salt and several other ingredients to produce a thick, red, flavorful sauce. Guajillo chilies may be used in pastes, butters, or rubs to flavor all kinds of meats, especially chicken. Alternatively, they can be added to salsas to create a sweet side dish with a surprisingly hot finish. In its dried form, chiles can keep for months in a dry, cool place.
longDescription: AUTHENTIC DRIED GUAJILLO CHILES - Guajillo chiles have a sweet, fruity, tangy, smoky flavor profile with notes of berries and tea. The Guajillo Chile is the dried form of Mirasol Chile. ADD MILD HEAT TO YOUR DISHES - Guajillo chiles have a mild heat, registering 2,500 to 5,000 on the Scoville scale. The Guajillo chile is one of the most used chile peppers in Mexican gastronomy to give color and flavor to sauces, moles, marinades, and a lot of other stews. GROWN IN THE FIELDS OF MEXICO - Grown in the beautiful fields of Mexico to ensure freshness and authenticity. Our chiles are sourced from real farmers to bring authentic and fresh chiles to your table. ALL NATURAL, NO CHEMICALS - Our recipe includes NO preservatives, additives, or chemicals to ensure real freshness. Quality is our foremost priority! PACKED WITH CARE - Our Guajillo chilies are hand-selected and hand-packed in our gourmet spice shop. For optimum flavor and freshness, we recommend washing all chiles before being consumed.

name: Dried Chipotle Chile Peppers - Whole - 1.5 oz Resealable Bag by Ole Rico
shortDescription: Chipotle Chiles are an authentic product sourced from the best spice houses in Mexico. They are dry smoked jalapeño peppers used in many authentic Mexican dishes, as well as an added ingredient to salsas, chili, meats, soups, BBQ, etc. Chipotle Chile Peppers are 2 to 4 inches in length, about 1 inch wide. Because of how Chipotle Chile peppers are processed, they come with a more "fruity" and rich, smokey flavor with a medium hot profile, typically categorized on a 5,000 to 10,000 Scoville Scale. Chipotle is often a key ingredient in a recipe that imparts a relatively mild but earthy spiciness to many dishes in Mexican cuisine.
longDescription: AUTHENTIC DRIED MORITA CHILES - The chipotle chile is one of the most popular chilies at a national and international level and without a doubt a condiment that most of the people of Mexico love and know. ADD FLAVOR TO YOUR DISHES - One of the most popular dishes prepared with these chilies is the famous Tinga, a Mexican dish made with shredded chicken in a sauce made from tomatoes, chipotle chilis in adobo, and sliced onions. GROWN IN THE FIELDS OF MEXICO - Grown in the beautiful fields of Mexico to ensure freshness and authenticity. name: Fresh Cut Culantro, 0.5 oz Clamshell
shortDescription: Add delicious flavor to your dishes with Fresh Cut Culantro. Commonly used in Latin, Indian, and Asian cooking, culantro is similar to cilantro but with a much stronger taste profile. When using culantro, use half as much as you would cilantro. Culantro pairs well with spicy dishes to balance out the heat. Chopped leaves are often used to garnish dishes, while the stems are used to flavor soups and sauces. Add culantro to salsas, chutneys, pesto, marinades, and dressings. You can even add it to your salads for an extra boost of flavor. Culantro makes a great addition to cooked meals, too, as it adds depth of flavor. Add culantro to tacos, falafel, burger patties, soups, broths, curries, or mix it into a stir fry. Fresh Cut Culantro is a versatile herb that no home cook should be without.

name: Fresh Basil, 1.5 oz Clamshell
shortDescription: Peppery, sweet, and savory, Fresh Basil is the herb you should never be without. This royal herb can basil-cally be added to anything from bruschetta to pasta. For a note of freshness, add just before serving! Just triple the amount you’d use for dried basil. No fridge, please! Basil is happiest at room temperature, hanging out in your kitchen. High in vitamin K and manganese, is there anything this herb can’t do? Top a pizza, finely chop and mix with olive oil and other herbs for a delectable dipping oil, craft a mouthwatering caprese salad, or whip up a pesto that will have your family saying you’re the best-o. No matter how you use it, Fresh Basil will give your dishes a zingy fresh taste.
longDescription: Fresh basil Peppery, sweet, and savory Perishable Rinse before use Store at room temperature
